caption: Very clean and convenient place. They provide generous meals and for affordable prices. We liked the meals very much and the waiters were very attentive and informative. Will definitely recommend this restaurant.

Old world Italian flavors at the original Rosebud on Taylor street. The Stacked Eggplant is listed under "salads" but I made a meal of it. Two tall stacks of the crispiest fried eggplant ever topped with a slice of fresh mozzarella, tomato and topped with arugula. My friend had the perfectly sauced meat lasagna. Friendly, welcoming staff added to the great experience. Note: it’s a favorite spot for dinner before a Blackhawks game. So make a reservation on those late afternoon game days.

The reason I give it 3 stars is because the people that had pasta dishes really liked their food, and they had a "special" off menu appetizer of stuffed peppers, which were really good.  Also, the table next to us order Halibut and the portion size was awesome. And the 2 pork chops I had were of good proportion. Made a 6:30 reservation for 2 on valentines day expected a bit of a wait but it was way worse than I could imagine. We were promptly there at 6:25 and then we were seated. We then got waters and my fiance got a glass of wine after that the service went down hill. After getting the wine we placed our order for one steak with potato, one pasta dish and an appetizer. We waited about 30 min for the appetizer but it still had not come so we decided to give the kitchen time because we saw how many guest were there. We then waited another half an hour but still not a thing came to our table. By then we noticed the other customers still hadn't got their food as well. After about 15 min we finally got our shrimp which was great so we thought the night was turning around. As we finished the shrimp we expected our food to come soon after but it still had not come. After this my fiance and I noticed the couple to the right of us asked to get their food to go because they couldn't wait any longer because like us they had other plans. So we then flagged down our waiter and asked to do the same. The food took about an extra 30 minutes and then finally we were able to leave. After all of this I dont believe the free slice of cake really made up for the service at all. I'm quite sad because my fiance was really excited to have a great and romantic night but we left the restaurant hungry and disappointed.

We ate here at the recommendation of a co-worker and were not disappointed. Upon walking into this Italian restaurant it was like we had been transported back into an old gangster movie and I somewhat expected to see Al Capone having dinner at a table in the back. The decor, while very Italian, was tastefully done and really added to the restaurant.  Their menu had all the classical Italian dishes. We ordered some calamari and fried shrimp for an appetizer. I was somewhat disappointed by it as the calamari seemed to be slightly under cooked and the spicy sauce that was served with it did very little to accent the food.  For the main course I went with the special and had the Chilean sea bass. This part of the meal was very good and I had no complaints. The dish had a very good mix of flavors and spices leading to a very nice meal.  The tiramisu was absolutely enormous and I was only able to eat a little of it before asking for a box to take it with me.  We were somewhat surprised with the cost of the meal as the menu prices seemed reasonable. I would advise people eating on a budget to avoid the specials as they were more expensive than what was listed on the menu.
